   specimens deposited in herbaria, a new species, Glochidion shanense Gang
   Yao \& Shixiao Luo (Phyllantheae, Phyllanthaceae), is here described and
   illustrated. The species is morphologically most similar to G.
   ellipticum Wight, but can be distinguished from the latter by having
   hairy branchlets, longer pedicels, uniseriate and narrowly triangular
   sepals of female flowers, 4-5-locular ovaries, stout and cylindric
   persistent style on fruits.},
